<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TolE001">
        <l>eḻutteṉap paṭupa</l>
        <l>vakaramuta ṉakara viṟuvāy</l>
        <l>muppaḵ teṉpa</l>
        <l>cārntuvaraṉ marapiṉ mūṉṟalaṅ kaṭaiyē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
          <l>Those which are termed the <foreign xml:lang="ta">eḻuttu</foreign><note place="foot">The
            term <foreign xml:lang="ta">eḻuttu</foreign> means : (1) sound (phone, <foreign xml:lang="de">Laut</foreign>), (2) phoneme, (3) letter (graphic symbol, grapheme).
            In the 1st line, obviously, <foreign xml:lang="ta">eḻuttu</foreign> stands for graphic
            representation of the phoneme (since the ' secondary ' sounds are excluded from the term <foreign xml:lang="ta">eḻuttu</foreign>).</note> are said to be</l>
        <l>thirty in number</l>
        <l>beginning with <foreign xml:lang="ta">a</foreign></l>
        <l>[and] ending with <foreign xml:lang="ta">ṉ</foreign></l>
        <l>except the three the occurrence of which</l>
        <l>depends upon others.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
